;What is Push?
Tge è Push?


;Push is an optional feature that allows websites to send you messages even when you aren’t visiting the site.
Push è ina funcziun opziunala che permetta a websites da ta trametter messadis era sche ti visitas gist in'autra website.


;Sites can use this feature to provide you with notifications or update data in the background.
Websites pon duvrar questa funcziun per ta preschentar communicaziuns u actualisar datas en il fund davos.


;For instance, a webmail site might use Push to provide you with a notification when new messages arrive, or a weather site might use Push to provide storm alerts.
Per exempel po ina website da webmail utilisar Push per t'infurmar cura ch'in nov messadi arriva, u ina pagina cun las previsiuns da l'aura po t'alarmar en cas da stemprads.


;You will only receive messages from sites for which you have granted permission.
Ti retschaivas mo messadis da websites che han tia lubientscha per ta trametter avis.


;How does it work?
Co funcziuna quai?


;Firefox maintains a connection to a push service.
Firefox mantegna ina connexiun ad in servetsch da push.


;Sites that you have granted permission for Push can use the service to send you messages.
Websites che han tia lubientscha per Push pon utilisar il servetsch per ta trametter messadis.


;Firefox delivers this push message to a small piece of JavaScript called a “worker”.
Firefox furnescha quest messadi Push ad ina pitschen toc da JavaScript, numnà “worker”.


;The worker then processes the message.
Worker elavurescha lura il messadi.


;It might decide to show a visual notification or store the message for later use.
Ussa po vegnir visualisà in avis u ch'il messadi vegn arcunà per l'utilisar pli tard.


;What information do I share with a site?
Tgeninas infurmaziuns cundivid jau cun ina website?


;A site can use Push to send you a message at any time, even when you are not actively visiting it.
Ina website po utilisar Push per ta trametter in messadi da tut temp, era sche ti na la visitas betg activamain en quel mument.


;A site that sends you a message can learn your IP address if it chooses to do so; this could reveal your location.
Ina website che ta trametta in messadi po vegnir a savair tia adressa IP sch'ella vul; quai po tradir tes lieu.


;What information does Firefox use to provide Push?
Tgeninas infurmaziuns dovra Firefox per offrir Push?


;Firefox maintains a permanent connection to a push service in order to receive push messages.
Firefox mantegna ina connexiun permanenta cun in servetsch da push per pudair recepir messadis da push.


;On our server we store a randomized identifier for your browser, along with a randomized identifier for each site you authorize.
Sin noss server memorisain nus in identificatur casual per tes navigatur, dasper in identificatur casual per mintga website che ti autoriseschas.


;On Firefox for desktop, the push service is operated by Mozilla.
En Firefox per computers è il servetsch Push gestiunà da Mozilla.


;Firefox for Android uses the same <a href="%s">Google Cloud Messaging</a> platform and infrastructure that your other Android applications use.
Firefox per Android utilisescha la plattafurma ed infrastructura da <a href="%s">Google Cloud Messaging</a> che era tias autras applicaziuns dad Android dovran.


;In both cases, the push service cannot decrypt your push messages.
En omadus cas na po il servetsch da push betg decriptar tes messadis da push.


;Push messages are encrypted, only your copy of Firefox can decipher them.
Messadis da push èn criptads. Mo tia copia da Firefox als po decriptar.


;The encrypted messages are stored on the server until they are delivered.
Il server arcunescha ils messadis criptads enfin ch'el als po spedir.


;How do I revoke Push permissions?
Co poss jau revocar las permissiuns per Push?


;To stop a site from sending you push messages:
